programme.title: Breakfast
programme.desc: A round-up of national and international news, plus sports reports, weather forecasts and arts and entertainment features.

programme.title: Match of the Day
programme.desc: Gary Lineker is joined by Jermaine Jenas to present highlights of the latest Premier League matches, including Manchester City v Newcastle United at the Etihad Stadium and Crystal Palace v West Bromwich Albion at Selhhurst Park. The Citizens were expecting to maintain their strong start to the domestic campaign against struggling Newcastle, while West Brom manager Tony Pulis' side faced a tough task away to one of his former clubs. Plus, Aston Villa v Stoke City, Bournemouth v Watford, Norwich City v Leicester City, Sunderland v West Ham United and Chelsea v Southampton.

programme.title: The Andrew Marr Show
programme.desc: The broadcaster presents an edition of the political current affairs show live from the Conservative Party Conference in Manchester, where guest contributors include Prime Minister David Cameron, and Wolf Hall actor Mark Rylance.

programme.title: Sunday Morning Live
programme.desc: Sian Williams hosts a discussion of designing babies and cures for loneliness. Hardeep Singh Kohli talks to Mary Wilson of The Supremes about her faith and the death of her son.

programme.title: Sunday Politics
programme.desc: The week's events at Westminster, presented by Andrew Neil. Including news and a regional round-up.

programme.title: MOTD2 Extra
programme.desc: Mark Chapman and guests discuss yesterday's Premier League matches and preview Everton v Liverpool, Arsenal v Manchester United and Tottenham Hotspur v Swansea City.

programme.title: Bargain Hunt
programme.desc: Experts Charlie Ross and Catherine Southon head to an antiques and collectibles fair at Epsom Downs Racecourse in Surrey to assist two teams in their search for valuable items. Plus, presenter Tim Wonnacott visits Petworth House, West Sussex, to view its extensive collection of sculptures.

programme.title: The Great British Bake Off
programme.desc: The remaining bakers get to grips with chocolate in the semi finals, making chocolate tarts for their signature challenge, a chocolate souffle for the technical bake and chocolate centrepieces for the showstopper. As always, the contestants are tasked with producing something that looks and tastes good, before judges Mary and Paul cast a critical eye over their efforts. Presented by Mel Giedroyc and Sue Perkins.

programme.title: Eat Well for Less
programme.desc: The Guests from Loughborough eat a diet of convenience food that is not only unwholesome, it is also very expensive. Mum Lisa is aware she has to make her family more healthy, but is going about it the wrong way, buying into costly `superfoods' rather than good old-fashioned fruit and veg. Can Gregg and Chris help the Guests bring more variety to their plates - and in turn, knock a whopping 50 per cent off their shopping bill? Along the way, they also investigate how canned fish compares to fresh and which oil is best for cooking, as well as the diet cons to watch out for. Last in the series.

programme.title: Points of View
programme.desc: Viewers' opinions on BBC shows, a chance to see memorable clips, and an insight into what goes on behind the scenes of new programmes.

programme.title: Songs of Praise
programme.desc: Aled Jones visits Ely Cathedral to attend the annual pet service, and former Westlife singer Shane Filan provides a life update before taking part in a special solo performance.

programme.title: The Great British Bake Off: The Class of 2014
programme.desc: A look back at series five's most momentous events, from Luis Troyano's 3D biscuit construction to the now-infamous moment when Iain Watters' threw his unsalvagable baked Alaska in the bin. The heated 2014 contest eventually ended in a win for East Yorkshire's Nancy Birtwhistle, and here, all the contestants are given a chance to speak about their time in the tent, and share what they have been up to since the competition ended. Presented by Mel Giedroyc and Sue Perkins.

programme.title: Countryfile
programme.desc: Anita Rani and Helen Skelton head for the north-west of Lancashire to visit the coast of Morecambe Bay, where Anita takes a cycle ride near Silverdale - a stretch of the Bay famous for its sunsets. She also takes a detour to Leighton Moss RSPB reserve, where the black tailed godwits are putting on a spectacular autumn show. While Anita takes in the county's avian wonders, Helen treks across the sands with the daring kayakers who take on some of the fastest tides in the UK. Plus, Matt Baker is in North Wales for the third of the show's Children in Need ramble films. Adam Henson get to grips with a herd of dexter cattle, Tom Heap sets out to build a badger-proof farm, and John Craven announces the winner of this year Countryfile photographic competition. Including Weather for the Week Ahead.

programme.title: Strictly Come Dancing: The Results
programme.desc: Tess Daly and Claudia Winkleman return to host the results show, which will see the two couples with the lowest scores facing the dreaded dance-off. The make-or-break performances will help the judges decide who deserves to stay in the competition - and who will be leaving so early in the contest. There will also be music by Rod Stewart, and a quick analysis of Saturday's performances in Len's Lens.

programme.title: Antiques Roadshow
programme.desc: Fiona Bruce presents the show from Durham Cathedral, where she examines a collection of rare books, including an early version of the Magna Carta, and John Axford examines a rare 19th-century plate. Objects brought in to be valued include a carriage clock found on a bomb site, an early drawing by Laura Knight, a 19th-century missionary's medical kit and a collection of football memorabilia.

programme.title: From Darkness
programme.desc: New series. Former Greater Manchester Police officer Claire Church's peaceful existence in the Western Isles is shattered when four bodies linked to her previous investigations are unearthed. DCI John Hind suspects the bodies are connected to a case that dates back to 1998 and the subsequent inquiry forces Claire to revisit her troubled past in law enforcement, and drags her back into a world she thought she had left behind for good. Psychological crime drama, written by Katie Baxendale, and starring Anne-Marie Duff.

programme.title: Match of the Day 2
programme.desc: Mark Chapman reviews the day's Premier League action, featuring Everton v Liverpool, Arsenal v Manchester United and Swansea City v Tottenham Hotspur. The Reds were aiming to extend their unbeaten run against their Merseyside rivals to 11 matches, while the Gunners were looking to avenge a 2-1 defeat at the hands of United in last season's corresponding fixture. Spurs went into their contest boasting an excellent record against the Swans, having not lost to them since 1991. With analysis from Alan Shearer and Ian Wright.

programme.title: The Women's Football Show
programme.desc: Jacqui Oatley and guests review the conclusion to the FA WSL season, with fixtures including Manchester City Ladies Notts County Ladies and Chelsea Ladies v Sunderland Ladies.

programme.title: This Is BBC Two
programme.desc: Preview of upcoming programmes from BBC Two.

programme.title: The Instant Gardener
programme.desc: Helen Skelton and designer Danny Clarke have just one day to transform a grey and windswept roof terrace in Basingstoke into a cosy and colourful outdoor room for owner Aimee.

programme.title: Countryfile
programme.desc: Matt Baker and Ellie Harrison present this year's One Man and His Dog competition, from Chirk Castle, North Wales, with shepherding talent from Scotland, Ireland, England and Wales competing. Ellie also investigates the history of the castle and the conservation work being carried out in the area, as well as examining the increasing popularity of the Welsh sheepdog among shepherds.

programme.title: Gardeners' World
programme.desc: Joe Swift meets fashion designer Zandra Rhodes, who explains how the flowers she likes to grow have influenced her work over the years. Plus, in the second of her films about botany, Carol Klein goes underground to unravel the mysteries of roots and explain why they are so important to the health of plants. Presented by Monty Don.

programme.title: The Beechgrove Garden
programme.desc: Jim McColl and Carole Baxter point out colourful plant combinations for this time of year, before he prepares half-hardy perennials for winter and she shows how to dry off amaryllis bulbs. George Anderson meets Alec West in Coldstream, who has an orchard jam-packed with apples, pears and plums - his fruit collection is believed to be the biggest in the country.

programme.title: Saturday Kitchen Best Bites
programme.desc: James Martin presents highlights of the series, recalling his favourite moments from previous years in the kitchen.

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The two remaining Central region chefs cook all four courses again for judges Prue Leith, Oliver Peyton and Matthew Fort, who are joined in their deliberations by Helen Carey, former chair of the WI. Together, the arbiters decide which chef to send through to represent the region in the national finals.

programme.title: Live Athletics
programme.desc: The Great Scottish Run. Coverage of the half-marathon staged in Glasgow, which is the largest mass-participation event in Scotland, with thousands of people taking part and raising money for charity, as well as international athletes competing in the elite events. Stephen Mokoka was the winner of the men's race last year, while Edna Kiplagat claimed victory in the women's race. Dougie Vipond presents, with commentary by Rob Walker, Brendan Foster and Liz McColgan, and reports from David Currie and Rhona McLeod.

programme.title: NFL Live
programme.sub-title: Miami Dolphins v New York Jets
programme.desc: Miami Dolphins v New York Jets (Kick-off 2.30pm). Coverage of the week four match from Wembley Stadium, where the AFC East rivals face each other, in what will be the first of three fixtures to take place in London this season. The Dolphins appeared in the first international series match at this stadium in 2007 when they lost to the New York Giants, and also played here last year, on which occasion they defeated the Oakland Raiders 38-14. This should ensure they are accustomed to the rigours of travelling across the Atlantic and preparing properly for this game, whereas this will be a new experience for the Jets having not played in here before. Nat Coombs presents, with analysis from mike Carlson and Osi Umenyiora.

programme.title: Super League Play-Offs
programme.desc: Tanya Arnold introduces action from the Million Pound Game, which decided who claimed the final place in next season's Super League. Plus, the key moments from the Super League semi-finals.

programme.title: Patagonia: Earth's Secret Paradise
programme.desc: The documentary offering a glimpse into the rarely seen South American wilderness continues, this time following the path of the relentless wind sweeping east through Patagonia's dry desert from the Andes' peaks. The programme reveals a weird world of maras - a large relative of the guinea pig - and penguins, and witnesses the first faltering steps of baby guanacos - Patagonia's very own camels. Cameras also observe the people who have taken on this inhospitable environment and carved out a home for themselves. Santiago Cabrera narrates.

programme.title: Licence to Thrill - Paul Hollywood Meets Aston Martin
programme.desc: The Great British Bake-Off's Paul Hollywood hangs up his baker's apron to indulge his other passion, Aston Martin cars, which he has been obsessed with ever since he received a toy model of the Aston Martin DB5 driven by Sean Connery's Bond in Goldfinger. Paul is given a chance to test-drive the DBR1, which won the 1959 24 Hours of Le Mans championship, the DB5 he has cherished since childhood, and the DB10, which features as 007's new vehicle in the latest Bond film Spectre. The baker is also given a chance to join one of Aston's racing teams, and hear from the company's new boss Andy Palmer, who discusses his plans to improve the brand's financial fortunes.

programme.title: Special Forces - Ultimate Hell Week
programme.desc: Andrew Flintoff brings the contenders home for the final challenge, as they undertake 48 hours of gruelling training with the British SAS. The six recruits are confronted with an assortment of intense physical and mental challenges that few serving soldiers are selected for and even fewer succeed at. At the end of the training, a final winner is chosen. Last in the series.

programme.title: Family Guy
programme.desc: Joe decides to embrace life by quitting his job with the police and taking the guys on a road trip to the Niagara Falls, where he makes an unexpected decision.

programme.title: Family Guy
programme.desc: Bobby Briggs, the criminal who crippled Joe years before, breaks out of jail - but he does not bargain on the community's hostile reception, as Quagmire, Joe and Peter unite to hunt him down. Meanwhile, Brian grows jealous when Lois gets a cat to look after.

programme.title: Family Guy
programme.sub-title: Lois Comes Out of Her Shell
programme.desc: Lois is not looking forward to her birthday, so she decides to turn her life around by adopting a different, younger lifestyle, growing her hair and having a makeover on a shopping trip. Meanwhile, Stewie finds a turtle at the park and adopts him as a new pet.

programme.title: Top Coppers
programme.sub-title: The Chill of the Cockney Freezer
programme.desc: New series. Police crime drama spoof, following the exploits of detectives John Mahogany and his partner Mitch Rust as they attempt to liberate the fictional Justice City from the residents of its deranged criminal underworld. The series begins as the duo tackle Cockney gangster Harry McCrane (Friday Night Dinner's Paul Ritter), who has procured an ice-cream factory, and is using it to a front for his drug-dealing business. Mahogany also face the daunting prospect cancelling his planned video night with Rust in favour of a date with new girl Pippa. Starring Steen Raskopoulos and John Kearns. Previously seen on BBC Three.

programme.title: Lucky Them
programme.desc: Premiere. A journalist is given the job of tracking down a rock star who vanished from the public eye years previously. The writer once had a relationship with the singer, and delves into her own past in order to find him, discovering her own painful memories have now become part of his legend. Comedy drama, starring Toni Collette, Thomas Haden Church and Oliver Platt.

programme.desc: Surreal children's fun based on the comic book.

programme.desc: Ten-year-old Trek becomes obsessed with dinosaurs - and finds them everywhere.

programme.title: Signed Stories: Share a Story
programme.desc: A look behind the scenes of the Share a Story competition, meeting the competitors and the animators who turned their stories into short films.

programme.title: Sooty
programme.desc: Further adventures with ever-popular puppet pals Sooty, Sweep and Soo.

programme.title: Fish Hooks
programme.desc: The adventures of three goldfish - Milo, Oscar and Bea - who attend Freshwater High, a school submerged in a large tank in the middle of a pet store.

programme.title: Matt Hatter Chronicles
programme.desc: Children's animation, following the adventures of the 13-year-old as he battles memorable villains from movies, myth and legend.

programme.title: Marvel Avengers Assemble
programme.desc: Animated super hero adventures.

programme.title: Horrid Henry
programme.desc: Cartoon about a mischievous youngster who delights in playing pranks, being rotten to his relatives and generally getting up to no good.

programme.title: Thunderbirds Are Go
programme.desc: The Tracy brothers and their friends at International Rescue set out to foil the nefarious plots of the evil Hood. An updated remake of the classic 1960s marionette adventure series, this time featuring computer-animated characters on live-action modeled sets. With the voices of Rosamund Pike, Kayvan Novak and Thomas Brodie-Sangster, with the original Parker - David Graham - returning to voice Lady Penelope's long-serving chauffeur.

programme.title: Murder, She Wrote
programme.desc: The amateur sleuth investigates the murder of a tennis player's boyfriend, who was killed by a bomb planted in the sportswoman's car. Linda Hamilton (The Terminator) and Bryan Cranston (Breaking Bad) guest star.

programme.title: The Jeremy Kyle Show
programme.desc: The host invites guests to air their differences over family and relationship issues, and provides them with his own brand of no-nonsense advice.

programme.title: The Jeremy Kyle Show

programme.title: Rugby World Cup
programme.desc: Argentina v Tonga (Kick-off 2.30pm). Coverage of the Pool C encounter from Leicester City Stadium, as the teams face each other for the first time in their history. The Pumas will expect to record a victory in this match, and also claim one of the top two positions in the pool that guarantees a place in the quarter-finals, while Tonga will likely battle for third place and an automatic spot in the 2019 World Cup. Argentina's best-ever performance at a World Cup came in 2007 when they went on to finish third, and they have reached the knockout stage on three occasions in total, whereas Tonga have never made it beyond the pool stage. Presented by John Inverdale, with analysis from Brian O'Driscoll, Lawrence Dallaglio and George Gregan, and commentary by Martin Gillingham and Shane Williams.

programme.title: Rugby World Cup
programme.desc: Ireland v Italy (Kick-off 4.45pm). Coverage of the third Pool D match for both teams, which takes place at the Olympic Stadium in London. This is only the second-ever World Cup fixture between these nations, with the previous one having taken place at the 2011 tournament in New Zealand. That was also a pool-stage match, and Ireland's comprehensive 36-6 victory at Otago Stadium in Dunedin ensured they would top Pool C having won all four of their games, though their subsequent quarter-final match against Wales saw their run come to an end as they lost 22-10. Presented by John Inverdale, with analysis from Brian O'Driscoll, Lawrence Dallaglio and George Gregan, and commentary by Jon Champion, Geordan Murphy and Ben Kay.

programme.title: The X Factor
programme.desc: The first stage of this year's three-part Six Chair Challenge arrives, in which judges Simon Cowell, Rita Ora, Nick Grimshaw and Cheryl Fernandez-Versini are given the opportunity to pick six acts to champion through to the later stages of the contest. The format has the potential to generate a great deal of drama in the studio, as the judges have the right to switch acts in and out of their line-up whenever they choose. Girl group 4th Power, 17-year-old singer Louisa Johnson and youth worker Monica Michael are among the would-be stars who have already secured a place in this round of the contest, but it remains to be seen whether any of them will be able to win over the panel and progress further.

programme.title: Downton Abbey
programme.desc: Mr Carson and Mrs Hughes' wedding is fast approaching, but a misunderstanding threatens to derail the occasion, and when the big day arrives it also brings a few unexpected guests. Meanwhile, Edith reconnects with an old acquaintance, who comes to her aid in her hour of need, and over at the Dower House, Spratt has something to hide, meaning Denker is hot on his trail. Daisy jumps to conclusions about one of the countess's plots, and tensions mount over the hospital takeover, prompting Isobel to offend a friend. Period drama, starring Jim Carter, Phyllis Logan, Elizabeth McGovern and Laura Carmichael.

programme.title: Rugby World Cup Highlights
programme.sub-title: Argentina v Tonga and Ireland v Italy
programme.desc: Argentina v Tonga and Ireland v Italy. Action from the latest pool matches, which took place at Leicester City Stadium and the Olympic Stadium respectively. While Ireland and Italy have faced each other on numerous occasions in the past as part of the annual Six Nations championship, Argentina and Tonga were meeting for the first time. Presented by Mark Durden-Smith, with analysis from David Flatman, Maggie Alphonsi and Geordan Murphy.

programme.title: Perspectives: The Great American Love Song with Nicky Campbell
programme.desc: Broadcaster Nicky Campbell embarks on a musical journey to Manhattan, where he reveals his lifelong passion for the music of 1920s and 1930s New York. He chooses six timeless love songs from the era, and finds out about the artists who wrote them - from George Gershwin, the gifted prodigy son of Jewish immigrants, to Cole Porter, the sparkling socialite with a secret double life. Nick's chosen songs are Manhattan, The Man I Love, Ain't Misbehavin', Night and Day, The Way You Look Tonight, and The Night We Called it a Day. With contributions from singers Annie Lennox, Michael Feinstein and Baba Brinkman.

programme.title: Fifteen to One
programme.desc: Sandi Toksvig hosts the general knowledge quiz, in which 15 contestants are pitted against one another in the hope of securing a place in the end-of-series final when a £40,000 jackpot will be up for grabs.

programme.title: How I Met Your Mother
programme.desc: Lily secretly applies for an art scholarship, while Ted receives a phone call from a dating agency claiming to have found his perfect match. However, he is forced to put the idea on hold because of his ever-present feelings for Robin. Meanwhile, Barney's prank war steps up a gear.

programme.title: How I Met Your Mother
programme.desc: Ted discovers Robin is going on a camping trip with her smarmy colleague Sandy Rivers, and decides to make a last-ditch attempt to win her love - with some help from one of Barney's ex-girlfriends. Meanwhile, Marshall is distraught when he discovers Lily has applied for a fellowship in San Francisco.

programme.title: Caterham Motorsport
programme.desc: Action from a recent race at Oulton Park, as the season continued for the iconic lightweight sports cars.

programme.title: Everybody Loves Raymond
programme.desc: Part one of two. Marie surprises everyone by arranging a trip to Rome for the whole family, but all Ray can do is complain. Comedy, starring Ray Romano, Doris Roberts and Patricia Heaton.

programme.title: Everybody Loves Raymond
programme.desc: Part two of two. As the family's Roman holiday continues, Robert falls in love with sultry local beauty Stefania (Alex Meneses), who works in an ice-cream shop.

programme.title: Frasier
programme.desc: The Seattle shrink finds out he is going to receive a lifetime achievement award, but a letter of congratulations from his mentor plunges him into an emotional crisis. Comedy, starring Kelsey Grammer.

programme.title: Frasier
programme.desc: The Seattle shrink takes his teenage son Frederick on a camping trip with Martin in a bid to rebuild their relationship. Comedy, starring Kelsey Grammer and John Mahoney.

programme.title: Sunday Brunch
programme.desc: The Vamps join Tim Lovejoy and Simon Rimmer to discuss their new single. Also on the show are comedian Patrick Kielty, scientist Alice Roberts and actress Lucy Speed.

programme.title: Channel 4 Racing: Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe
programme.desc: Nick Luck and Emma Spencer are at Longchamp in Paris to present live coverage of the prestigious feature race at 2.55, plus four other Group One races at 1.00, 1.35, 2.10 and 3.40. With reports by Simon Holt and Mick Fitzgerald.

programme.title: The Simpsons
programme.desc: Lisa is teased mercilessly by her classmates for having a weight problem. Marge learns school bully Nelson Muntz has never had a paternal role model and invites him to live with the family - much to Bart's dismay.

programme.title: School of Rock
programme.desc: A slobbish guitarist dreams of stardom, but his hopes are dashed when the other members of his band kick him out. Struggling to make ends meet, he takes a job as a supply teacher at an exclusive private school, and sets about moulding his pupils into rock gods. Comedy from director Richard Linklater, starring Jack Black, Joan Cusack, Mike White and Sarah Silverman.

programme.title: Channel 4 News
programme.desc: Including sport and weather.

programme.title: Homes by the Sea
programme.desc: New series. Charlie Luxton visits seaside properties across Britain to discover why so many people harbour dreams of owning a home by the sea. He begins his journey in Cornwall, where he visits a modern build on a cliff overlooking an old smugglers' cove in Portloe, and a listed engine house at Porthtowan. He also takes in a tithe barn in Bude, and discovers how an unsightly old building in Penzance found a new lease of life after being converted into a spacious apartment. Previously seen on More4.

programme.title: Cleopatra's Lost Tomb
programme.desc: An insight into the pioneering work of criminal lawyer-turned-archaeologist Dr Kathleen Martinez, who has made it her life's mission to locate the final resting place of Cleopatra, Egypt's last queen. Despite centuries of searching, very little evidence of the location of Cleopatra's tomb has ever been uncovered, but Kathleen's radical new theory on the queen's identity has led her to search where no-one else dared. Her hunch stunned the archaeological establishment as she uncovered a hidden network of tunnels and a vast city of the dead, as well as a 35-metre deep underground hole that bears all the hallmarks of a burial shaft.

programme.title: This Is England '90
programme.desc: Shane Meadows' gritty chronicle of working-class life in the Midlands concludes with this, the last entry in the the 1990-set tale, and the final part of the decade-spanning story of Woody, Lol, Shaun and friends. As winter arrives, there is a promise of new beginnings for Combo, Woody and Lol, but nothing is ever as simple as it seems. Shaun has grown into the man he was always meant to be, and Milky must deal with demons from his past. programme.title: Joy Division
programme.desc: On June 4 1976, four young men from ruined, post-industrial Manchester went to see a Sex Pistols show at the Manchester Lesser Free Trade Hall. Inspired by the gig that is now credited with igniting the Manchester music scene, they formed what was to become one of the world's most influential bands, Joy Division. Over thirty years later, despite a tragedy that was to cut them off in their prime, they are enjoying a larger audience and more influence than ever before, with a profound legacy that resonates fiercely in today's heavily manufactured pop culture. Featuring the participation of all the surviving band members, this film examines the band's story through never-before-seen live performance footage, personal photos, period films and newly discovered audiotapes. A fresh visual account of a unique time and place, this is the untold story of how four men transcended economic and cultural barriers to produce an enduring musical legacy, at a time of great social and political change.

Just as they are beginning to panic, Lola the inventor stumbles on a brilliant idea.

programme.title: ZingZillas: All the Fun of the Fair
programme.desc: A band of primate friends play music in their tropical island paradise and meet different musical guests. Zak wants to morris dance at the Island Fair, but where is he going to get the bells he needs for his ankles?.

programme.title: Something Special: We're All Friends: Dance
programme.desc: Using a sign language called Makaton, Something Special helps its audience learn how to communicate as well as develop their language in a fun and exciting way. Justin Fletcher presents songs, rhymes and visual humour all centred around themes that are familiar to young children. Justin travels near and far to meet new friends all over the country. Justin and his friends are having fun dancing, while Mr Tumble is outside getting sporty!.

programme.title: Meet the Pups
programme.desc: Series following a litter of puppies from birth to rehoming. The pups are growing up, and the pack dynamic is changing with every passing day. Mum and Dad are going to have to redraw some lines or embrace change.

programme.title: Minibeast Adventure with Jess: Centipede
programme.desc: Children's nature show. Jess and her friends explore the world of minibeasts. In her treehouse den, Jess has a close look at some centipedes - they are fierce hunters with lots of legs. Setting off on a minibeast adventure, she meets up with some children and together they search the garden for the creatures that live there. The children find a centipede and are able to have a good look at it, before building a cosy centipede corner where a centipede can hide away during the daytime.

programme.title: My Pet and Me: Guinea Pigs
programme.desc: Series showing children what it really means to have a pet. Ferne goes to a nursery in South London to meet class pets Buzz and Woody, who are very cuddly guinea pigs! The children and Ferne hide some food for them around the toys in their pen. They then go to the local pet shop to get Buzz and Woody's claws trimmed.

programme.title: Mike the Knight: Snow Dragon
programme.desc: Animated series about the adventures of a ten-year-old knight in training. Mike wants Squirt to get used to the snow, so he convinces him that his favourite storybook character, the Snow Dragon, is real. But when Squirt ends up stuck in a giant snowball, Mike learns not exaggerate to get what he wants.

programme.title: Tree Fu Tom: So Long Greenhorns
programme.desc: Animated fantasy adventure show. Tom and Twigs are in for a frenzied, rollercoaster day when they swap Spell School for running Ariela's ranch. Tom needs his friends and Big-World Magic help from the audience to calm the bedlam that's in store, and maybe they'll all discover that the grass isn't always greener.

programme.title: Chuggington: Undercover Action Chugger
programme.desc: Children's animation set in Chuggington, a special place where the trains talk, think and don't need drivers. Action Chugger goes undercover as an ordinary chugger and learns that it is hard work without his superpowers.

programme.title: Rastamouse: No Fix Fats
programme.desc: Stop-motion series featuring Rastamouse, Scratchy and Zoomer, crime-fighting special agents who solve mysteries and play in a reggae band. Fats is unable to cope with all the requests for assistance despite him promising immediate help to everyone phoning the 4x4 Garage. The Easy Crew must ensure the ingredients for the fruity ice get aboard the Jammin' Dodger, just in time for the summer party, whilst tracking down Fats to make sure that he is okay.

programme.title: Swashbuckle: Message in a Bottle: Finger Puppets
programme.desc: A group of children have sent Gem a message in a bottle to tell her about some homemade dancing finger puppets they have created. This reminds Gem of when Cook and Line were given a dancing lesson by Captain Sinker!.

programme.title: Justin's House: Hottyspottyitis
programme.desc: Justin Fletcher entertains a live audience of children with singing, dancing and comedy chaos. He is helped by Robert the robot butler, Little Monster and unicycling delivery lady Dee Livery. Every time Justin and Little Monster sneeze something messy happens in Justin's House. Helped by a doctor download, Robert does his best to cure the pair of their Hottyspottyitis.

programme.title: Footy Pups: Honesty
programme.desc: Preschool sports series. Rex learns that honesty is the best policy when he accidentally floods the pitch. Meanwhile, Rachel challenges the team with some honest questions.

programme.title: Kerwhizz: Vegetable Valley Alley
programme.desc: Kerwhizz is the quiz with added whizz where three teams answer questions and then race around weird and wonderful raceworlds. Join teams Ninki, Twist and Kit as they battle it out to win Mods for their racing Pods. A new and exciting raceworld may involve more weeding than whizzing for the teams and their trusty sidekicks, so they must use their Mods wisely.

programme.title: Swashbuckle: Weevils
programme.desc: Pirate-themed physical game show where a team of daring young Swashbucklers take on the naughty Cook, Line and Captain Sinker to win jewels for their treasure chest. Swashbucklers Callum, Samiullah, Daniel and Imaan take on the Coconutty Raft and Pirate Cannons in pursuit of Gem's jewels. The naughty pirates are plagued by weevils and the only way to lure them away is to tempt them with biscuits.

programme.title: Sarah and Duck: Cake Bake
programme.desc: Sarah and her best friend Duck embark on simple but exciting adventures, exploring the world both near and far in their own wobbly and imaginative way. It's Duck's birthday, so Sarah decides to bake a cake to celebrate.

programme.title: Katie Morag: Katie Morag and the Big Picture
programme.desc: Live-action children's show set in Scotland. Katie Morag loves doing big paintings. She and Liam are looking for a big piece of paper to paint on, but their parents are busy in the post office and can't help them find one. After asking Grannie Island without success, Katie Morag calls at the Lady Artist's house - she is bound to know where they could get one from!.

programme.title: Katie Morag: Grannie Island's Ceilidh - Annie Jessie and the Merboy
programme.desc: Live-action children's show set in Scotland. At Grannie Island's ceilidh, Uncle Matthew tells a story about a teenage girl called Annie Jessie who lived on Struay long ago. She works hard looking after her family. One day when sheltering from a storm she meets a merboy who has lost his comb. Annie Jessie makes him a new comb from a razor shell and soon they fall in love. With the help of the sea king, who is in charge of all the creatures of the sea, they are able to go and live happily together on the island of Fuay.

programme.title: Charlie and Lola: But I Am An Aligator
programme.desc: Children's animation. Charlie loves his little sister Lola, even if she can be exasperating at times. Dressing up is one of Lola's absolutely favourite things to do and now she has got this fabulous new alligator costume, she is not ever going to take it off - not ever! Charlie is very embarrassed when she wears it to the supermarket and the park, and when he hears she plans to wear it for a school talk called All About Me, he has to act quickly to change her mind.

programme.title: Waybuloo: De Li Gets Her Shoehorns on
programme.desc: Animated series set in the magical land of Nara, inhabited by the joyful and gentle Piplings. Lau Lau, Yojojo, De Li and Nok Tok learn Yogo, meet children and have fun. De Li loves Nok Tok's shoehorns. Nok Tok likes to share them with all the other Piplings. Lau Lau and Yojojo can't wait to try them, but De Li is nervous. She asks the others to go first.

programme.title: In the Night Garden: Oh Look! It's The Wottingers!
programme.desc: In a magical forest, colourful characters have adventures. The Wottingers call on the Pontipines, but there is no reply, so they decide to go looking for them. But the Pontipines were in after all, and go looking for the Wottingers.

programme.title: CBeebies Bedtime Stories: James Mcavoy - The Dinosaur That Pooped a Planet
programme.desc: An exciting story read by a special guest. James McAvoy reads The Dinosaur that Pooped a Planet and takes us on a space adventure with Danny and Dinosaur, but when Danny realises he's forgotten Dino's lunch box, the very hungry dinosaur eats everything in sight, including their only way home - the rocket!.

programme.title: The Other Pompeii: Life and Death in Herculaneum
programme.desc: Professor Andrew Wallace-Hadrill presents a documentary following the scientific investigation that aims to lift the lid on what life was like in the small Roman town of Herculaneum, moments before it was destroyed by a volcanic eruption. The investigation, based around the discovery of 12 arched vaults, reveals in great detail the lives of the ill-fated town's residents, and unique aerial photography gives a behind-the-scenes look at the town from the skies. With contributions from the forensic scientists leading the investigation, the film uncovers the minutiae of daily life in Herculaneum, including not just what residents ate but how they ate it, and why most of the skeletons found on the coast were men and those in the vaults, women and children.

programme.title: Woolly Mammoth: Secrets From the Ice
programme.desc: Professor Alice Roberts reveals the natural history of one the most famous of ice age animals - the woolly mammoth. Mammoths have transfixed humans since the depths of the last ice age, when their herds roamed across what is now Europe and Asia. Although these curious members of the elephant family have now been extinct for thousands of years, scientists can now paint an incredibly detailed picture of their lives thanks to whole carcasses that have been beautifully preserved in the Siberian permafrost. Alice meets scientists who are using the latest genetic, chemical and molecular tests to reveal the adaptations that allowed mammoths to evolve from their origins in the tropics to surviving the extremes of Siberia. In a dramatic end to the film, she helps unveil a brand new woolly mammoth carcass that may shed new light on our own ancestors' role in their extinction.

programme.title: Rome's Lost Empire
programme.desc: Dan Snow uses the latest satellite technology to reveal the secrets of the Roman Empire. Together with space archaeologist Sarah Parcak, Dan sets out to identify and then track down lost cities, amphitheatres and forts in an adventure that sees him travel through some of the most spectacular parts of the vast empire. Cutting-edge technology and traditional archaeology help build a better understanding of how Rome held such a large empire together for so long.

programme.title: TOTP 2 John Lennon Special
programme.desc: Yoko Ono introduces a special edition originally screened to mark what would have been John Lennon's 60th birthday. With anecdotes and reminiscences, Yoko introduces classics such as Give Peace a Chance, Power to the People, Instant Karma and Imagine.

programme.title: Jazz Piano Gold
programme.desc: Compilation of jazz piano performances dating from 1964 to 2009, featuring classics from Count Basie, Thelonious Monk, Oscar Peterson, Abdullah Ibrahim, Stan Tracey, Jacques Loussier, Duke Ellington, Return to Forever and Herbie Hancock taken from cult classic programmes such as Jazz 625, Show of the Week, Late Night Line Up, Love You Madly, Birdland, The Late Show and Later... with Jools Holland. Be it bebop, swing or contemporary, this is a must for all jazz piano fans.

programme.title: BBC Four Sessions: Georgie Fame - The Birth Of Cool
programme.desc: Series of unique concerts by musicians from around the world. Georgie Fame, who burst onto the scene in the 60s and continues to entertain fans with his cocktail of jazz and blues, plays a set at LSO St Luke's in London. Performing with him are some original members of his first band the Blue Flames, British trumpet impresario Guy Barker and Fame's sons James and Tristan. Features classics such as Yeh Yeh, Getaway and Flamingo Allnighter.

programme.title: The Cube
programme.desc: Student Isaac and Geordie mother-of-one Karen try to complete a series of increasingly difficult challenges, ranging from agility tests to skill trials, within the confines of The Cube - under pressure to hold their nerve as friends, family and the studio audience watch their every move. The further the contestants go in the competition, the more money they win, up to a jackpot of £250,000. Phillip Schofield hosts.

programme.title: Emmerdale
programme.desc: Omnibus. Suspicions run high in the village in the aftermath of the shooting. Diane and Victoria fear that Andy's sudden disappearance makes him look guilty. Chas receives a warning from Aaron to stay away from Chrissie, and struggles to remember being questioned, while Lawrence tries to keep the police from finding out about the gun. Paddy lies to Rhona, and Kirin tries to cheer Belle up.

programme.title: Coronation Street
programme.desc: Omnibus. A heartbroken Sally wallows in self-pity after Tim's reaction to her kiss with Kevin, so Rita gives her a dose of tough love, ordering her to buck herself up and sort the mess out before it's too late. The events of the past few days have left the Platts living in fear, while Yasmeen is furious to see Tracy walk free after the fire and visits the police, hoping she can convince them to revisit the case. Cathy is delighted when Roy invites her out to dinner - only to leave him waiting alone in the Bistro.

programme.title: The Almost Impossible Gameshow
programme.desc: Action-packed game show, with commentary from Irish comedy duo the Rubberbandits. Ten contestants are given 50 lives to take on a series of tricky challenges. The aim of the game is to complete five of them without losing all of their lives. Challenges include Tiny Bike, Dizzy Hurdle and Groin Croissant.

programme.title: You've Been Framed
programme.desc: Harry Hill narrates a selection of camcorder calamities and mobile-phone footage, featuring clips of cooking with gas, saddling up and something never before seen on the programme.

programme.title: Uncle Buck
programme.desc: An unreliable but good-natured slob is called upon to look after his trouble-making nephew and nieces while their parents are away - and what starts as a disaster soon changes for the better as the unlikely babysitter gets to grips with the finer points of being a responsible adult. Family comedy, starring John Candy, Macaulay Culkin, Jean Kelly, Gaby Hoffman, Amy Madigan and Laurie Metcalf. Including FYI Daily.

programme.title: Beethoven
programme.desc: An all-American family adopts a huge St Bernard, but the father is dismayed when it turns into a one-dog disaster zone. He insists the mutt must go to a new home, but when it is kidnapped by a crooked vet, dad has a change of heart and races to the rescue. Comedy, starring Charles Grodin, Bonnie Hunt, Oliver Platt and David Duchovny. Including FYI Daily.

programme.title: She's the Man
programme.desc: Soccer-mad Viola's football team is disbanded, and the only other side in the area is all-male - so she resorts to disguising herself as her twin brother to win a place on the squad. However, she falls for a team-mate who only has eyes for another girl - who in turn takes a liking to Viola in her male guise. Teenage romantic comedy, loosely based on Shakespeare's Twelfth Night, starring Amanda Bynes, Channing Tatum, Laura Ramsey and Vinnie Jones. Including FYI Daily.

programme.title: Stormbreaker
programme.desc: Teenager Alex Rider discovers his late uncle was a secret agent, and is assigned the task of completing his last mission - uncovering a criminal mastermind's plan to cause mayhem with a new kind of super-computer. Adventure based on Anthony Horowitz's novel, starring Alex Pettyfer, Bill Nighy, Mickey Rourke, Alicia Silverstone and Stephen Fry. Including FYI Daily.

programme.title: The Xtra Factor
programme.desc: Melvin Odoom and Rochelle Humes go back-stage to deliver all the behind-the-scenes gossip as the first round of six-chair challenges gets under way.

programme.title: American Pie: The Wedding
programme.desc: The friends from East Great Falls High reunite to celebrate Jim and Michelle's forthcoming wedding. Though reluctant to invite Stifler to their big day, the happy couple relent - but regret their decision when he plans a bachelor party on the same evening Jim is due to meet the in-laws. The third instalment in the comedy series, with Jason Biggs, Alyson Hannigan, Seann William Scott, Eddie Kaye Thomas and Eugene Levy. Including FYI Daily.

programme.desc: Text-based information service.

programme.title: Murder, She Wrote
programme.desc: Jessica sets out to clear a friend who has been arrested in connection with the murder of a crusading TV host - even though all the evidence suggests he is guilty. Guest starring Star Trek's George Takei.

programme.title: The Young Ones
programme.desc: A clean-cut teenager records a pop song in a bid to save his youth club, which a greedy tycoon wants to demolish so he can build an office block. Musical, starring Cliff Richard and the Shadows, with Robert Morley, Melvyn Hayes, Richard O'Sullivan and Carole Gray. Including FYI Daily.

programme.title: Heartbeat
programme.desc: The arrival of a traumatised and wounded stranger in Aidensfield coincides with the discovery of a woman's body on the moors, and sets off a treacherous chain of events that leaves one long-time resident's life hanging in the balance. Nicholas Farrell and Clare Holman guest star in the last-ever episode of the long-running police drama.

programme.title: Heartbeat
programme.desc: Part one of two. Mike faces a stressful time as he struggles to cope with his wife's departure, and Tricia offers him a shoulder to cry on, but is beset by problems of her own after prescribing birth control to a 16-year-old. Meanwhile, Sergeant Craddock finds his efforts to prepare for an important visit hampered by a series of attacks on the station, and Vernon makes a startling discovery in his bathtub. Jason Durr and Clare Calbraith star.

programme.title: Murder, She Wrote
programme.desc: Jessica enters the tough world of boxing, trying to clear her friend of murdering a devious fight manager - and deliver a knockout blow to the real culprit in the process. Ernest Borgnine (Airwolf) and Adam West (Family Guy) guest star.

programme.title: Inspector Morse
programme.desc: The Oxford detective faces a tough time while looking into a murder at a peaceful college. After suffering the familiar pangs of unrequited love, he clashes with the unpleasant college master and then unwittingly provides his main suspects with a watertight alibi. John Thaw and Kevin Whately star, with Robert Stephens, Amanda Burton and Philip Middlemiss.

programme.title: Ben-Hur
programme.desc: A Jewish prince in first-century Jerusalem is reunited with an old Roman friend, who is now the governor of Judea. However, their differing political views over local dissent leads to a bitter quarrel, and the governor uses the pretext of an accident to sell him into slavery and imprison his mother and sister. Years later, the prince returns, determined to seek revenge and find his missing family. Oscar-winning epic, starring Charlton Heston, Stephen Boyd and Haya Harareet. Including FYI Daily.

programme.title: Foyle's War
programme.desc: Sam and Foyle are shot at and almost run over by a speeding vehicle, and discover the incident is part of an illicit fuel racket. An undercover investigation reveals the detective's son Andrew to be involved, and the discovery that a driver at the petrol company has been murdered complicates matters further. Wartime drama, starring Michael Kitchen, Honeysuckle Weeks and Julian Ovenden.

programme.title: Sunday Night at the Palladium
programme.desc: Jimmy Carr hosts the variety show, featuring the cast of Beautiful: The Carole King Musical, with a medley of songs from the show, former Westlife singer Markus Feehily and one-time Strictly dancers Vincent Simone and Flavia Cacace. Hans Klok, who describes himself as the world's fastest illusionist, teaches Jimmy a few tricks, there's comedy from Rob Beckett, and further music from Rebecca Ferguson and 1980s chart stars Deacon Blue.

programme.title: Birds of a Feather
programme.desc: When Sharon and Tracey discover Dorien has been keeping a secret for more than 50 years, they decide to get involved, but the novelist is reluctant to confront her past. Meanwhile, Tracey finds motherhood isn't all it's cracked up to be. Sitcom, starring Pauline Quirke, Linda Robson and Lesley Joseph.

programme.title: City Lights
programme.desc: Howard moves out of the family home, hoping a temporary separation will help heal the rift in his marriage. Finding himself at a permanent loose end, he resorts to filling his time by watching TV with best pal Colin. Meanwhile, an increasingly dejected Pauline spends her first night with Tate - who finally manages to discover the address of the safe house.

programme.title: Private Benjamin
programme.desc: A scatterbrained society woman looks for a change of pace after her husband dies on their wedding night, and is tricked by a duplicitous recruiter into enlisting in the army. In spite of the initial culture shock and conflict with her tough commanding officer, she gradually finds direction and self-esteem for the first time in her life. Comedy, starring Goldie Hawn, Armand Assante, Eileen Brennan, Harry Dean Stanton and Sam Wanamaker. Including FYI Daily.

programme.title: Football's Greatest: Eusebio
programme.desc: A profile of the former Portuguese footballer, widely considered as one of the greatest strikers of all time having scored 317 goals for Benfica and 41 for his country.

programme.title: Ax Men
programme.desc: Documentary following the lives of lumberjacks in America's Pacific Northwest as they gear up for a new logging season and prepare to face the dangers of falling trees and heavy machinery.

programme.title: Ax Men
programme.desc: Browning gambles $30,000 on new equipment and two Aqua Loggers try to reel an enormous log.

programme.title: British Touring Car Championship Highlights
programme.desc: Steve Rider presents action from the ninth and penultimate round of the season from Silverstone, where the 25th, 26th and 27th races of the campaign were set to take place.

programme.title: MotoGP Highlights
programme.desc: The Grand Prix of Aragon. Action from the 14th round of the season at the Ciudad del Motor de Aragon in Spain.

programme.title: Tommy Cooper
programme.desc: Patrick Cargill and Trisha Noble join the incomparable comedian as he performs a variety of sketches.

programme.title: Rugby World Cup Greatest Moments
programme.desc: A selection of highlights from the history of the tournament, including England's historic victory in 2003 and Nelson Mandela handing over the trophy to Francois Pienaar in 1995. Presented by Martin Bayfield.

programme.title: Rugby World Cup Highlights
programme.desc: Action from the latest matches, featuring Argentina v Tonga in Pool C and Ireland v Italy in Pool D. Mark Durden-Smith presents, with analysis from Ugo Monye and Jason Robinson.

programme.title: Dunkirk

programme.title: Sex Diaries: Webcam Couples

Glenn and Ari are newlyweds who even webcammed on their honeymoon and don't charge viewers to watch them, while Emma and Eddie claim to make a six-figure salary. Kitty and Moses webcam as a way of making extra cash, performing one-on-one sex shows between cups of tea from the comfort of their own front room.

Aerial action adventure, starring Tom Cruise, Kelly McGillis, Val Kilmer, Anthony Edwards and Tom Skerritt.

Comedy, starring Jim Carrey, Jennifer Aniston and Morgan Freeman.

She swears to get revenge on him by placing a curse on his daughter, only to find herself developing a maternal bond with the girl. Fantasy adventure based on the story of Sleeping Beauty, starring Angelina Jolie, Elle Fanning, Sharlto Copley and Imelda Staunton.

programme.title: Treasure Island
programme.desc: An innkeeper's son discovers a map leading to notorious pirate Captain Flint's buried loot, and joins a seafaring expedition to find it. However, several of Flint's henchmen are among the crew, and under the leadership of the one-legged cook Long John Silver, they hatch a plan to steal the treasure. Disney adventure, based on Robert Louis Stevenson's novel, with Robert Newton and Bobby Driscoll.

programme.title: Snowball Express
programme.desc: A New York insurance accountant inherits a run-down hotel in the Colorado Rockies, and sets about transforming it into a successful ski resort with the help of his initially unwilling wife. Disney comedy, starring Dean Jones, Nancy Olson, Harry Morgan, Keenan Wynn and Johnny Whitaker.

programme.title: Oliver
programme.desc: Musical version of Charles Dickens' classic tale about a lonely workhouse orphan who ends up on the cold streets of London, where he falls under the wing of petty crook Fagin and his gang of young backstreet thieves. Starring Ron Moody, Mark Lester, Oliver Reed, Jack Wild, Harry Secombe, Shani Wallis and Leonard Rossiter.

programme.title: Maleficent Special
programme.desc: Alex Zane interviews the cast of the Disney fantasy movie telling the story of the evil sorceress from Sleeping Beauty.

programme.title: Mr Peabody & Sherman
programme.desc: A super-intelligent talking dog invents a time machine and adopts a human boy to assist with his experiments. The curious youngster cannot resist meddling with the invention - with disastrous results - and the duo have to journey into the past to undo the damage done to the course of history. Animated comedy, with the voices of Ty Burrell and Max Charles.

programme.title: The Last Song
programme.desc: A teenager is left angry and resentful after her parents divorce and her father moves away. Her mother decides to send her to spend the summer with her estranged dad, and over the course of the holiday, she gradually learns to bury the past, while also falling for a local boy. Drama, starring Miley Cyrus and Greg Kinnear.

programme.title: The Mask of Zorro
programme.desc: The sword-wielding saviour of Spanish California returns after 20 years in prison, tutoring a thief to take over his heroic role and tackle corrupt government officials, who are using slave labour to mine gold illegally. Both mentor and pupil have personal scores to settle with their enemies, led by a ruthless governor and a psychotic military officer. Swashbuckling adventure, with Anthony Hopkins, Antonio Banderas and Catherine Zeta-Jones.

programme.title: Dr Dolittle 3
programme.desc: The talented vet's daughter with the same uncanny ability to talk to animals is staying at a ranch. When she learns financial problems will force the place to close, she comes up with an ingenious idea to solve the crisis by training the livestock for a rodeo and winning $50,000. Comedy sequel, starring Kyla Pratt, Kristen Wilson and John Amos.

Comedy sequel, starring Kyla Pratt, Kristen Wilson and John Amos.

programme.title: Deep Family Secrets
programme.desc: A girl sets out on a personal quest to discover the truth about her mother's alleged abduction, and uncovers a tangled tale of adultery, incest and murder. Thriller, starring Richard Crenna, Angie Dickinson and Meg Foster.

programme.title: The Conversation
programme.desc: An obsessive surveillance expert makes the unprofessional mistake of getting personally involved in a dangerous case. Francis Ford Coppola's thriller, starring Gene Hackman, John Cazale, Robert Duvall, Allen Garfield and Harrison Ford.

programme.title: The Lives of Others
programme.desc: A secret service agent in 1980s East Germany spends his days dispassionately spying on and recording the activities of suspected enemies of the state. As he watches a celebrated playwright and his actress lover, he becomes increasingly obsessed with their daily lives - and learns a few secrets. Oscar-winning drama, starring Ulrich Muhe, Martina Gedeck and Sebastian Koch. In German.

programme.title: Marathon Man
programme.desc: A college undergraduate training for a marathon is drawn into a shady world of espionage by his secret agent brother and a Nazi war criminal searching for a cache of stolen diamonds - entangling the student in a plot involving kidnap, torture and political intrigue. John Schlesinger's thriller, starring Dustin Hoffman, Laurence Olivier and Roy Scheider. Based on the novel by William Goldman.

programme.title: The Sum of All Fears
programme.desc: The CIA becomes suspicious of Russia's nuclear activities, and agent Jack Ryan is ordered to investigate. However, it is not long before the threat of terrorists detonating a nuclear bomb on American soil is on the cards, sparking a race against the clock to avert disaster. Thriller based on Tom Clancy's novel, starring Ben Affleck, Morgan Freeman, James Cromwell, Liev Schreiber, Bridget Moynahan and Alan Bates.

programme.title: Jack Ryan: Shadow Recruit
programme.desc: A former soldier injured in the line of duty takes up a new career as a financial analyst for the CIA. However, his deskbound position changes to a dangerous undercover assignment when he discovers a plot to destroy the US economy. Spy thriller inspired by Tom Clancy's series of novels, starring Chris Pine, Keira Knightley, Kevin Costner and Kenneth Branagh, who also directed.

programme.title: The Recruit
programme.desc: A highly intelligent computer hacker is persuaded to join the CIA by a shady agent, who lets him think there is a link between the agency and his father's death. He proves he has a natural-born talent for espionage work, but when he is given a top-secret assignment to root out a mole within the training programme, he begins to believe his recruiter's warning that nothing is what it seems. Thriller, starring Al Pacino, Colin Farrell, Bridget Moynahan and Gabriel Macht.

programme.title: Spy Game
programme.desc: A veteran CIA agent is on the verge of retirement, but when he learns his former protege has been thrown into a Chinese prison and is awaiting execution, he decides to launch a perilous and ill-advised rescue attempt. Thriller, starring Brad Pitt, Robert Redford, Catherine McCormack and Stephen Dillane.

programme.title: Closed Circuit
programme.desc: A man stands trial for terrorism charges, but the evidence against him has been classified, so only one government-approved lawyer is allowed to see it. The attorney's ex-lover is appointed to handle the defence, and they agree to keep their past relationship a secret, but as the case unfolds, they are drawn together as evidence of a sinister conspiracy emerges. Thriller, starring Eric Bana, Rebecca Hall and Jim Broadbent.

programme.title: Conspiracy Theory
programme.desc: A paranoid New York taxi driver constantly regales his passengers with off-the-wall ideas about government cover-ups. However, when one of them turns out to be true, assassins are put on his trail to prevent the secret from being exposed. As he flees for his life, he seeks a government lawyer's help to find out which of his conspiracy theories is true. Thriller, starring Mel Gibson, Julia Roberts and Patrick Stewart.

programme.title: Treehouse
programme.desc: Two teenagers exploring a forest find an abandoned treehouse, where an injured girl is hiding. They discover she is from their home town and had recently gone missing, but before they can uncover what happened to her, the treehouse is besieged by the people who kidnapped her. Thriller, starring J Michael Trautmann and Dana Melanie.

programme.title: Predator
programme.desc: An elite military team on a top-secret mission in the jungles of Central America encounters a merciless alien hunter, which starts to pick the commandos off one by one. Sci-fi thriller, starring Arnold Schwarzenegger, Carl Weathers, Bill Duke, Sonny Landham, Jesse Ventura and Shane Black.

programme.title: Predator 2
programme.desc: A Los Angeles cop, working to bring down the city's drug gangs, suspects Jamaican criminals when he discovers several of his targets killed and skinned alive. However, the culprit behind the murders reveals himself to be an alien big-game hunter - with the stealth and guile to outwit the police and criminals alike. Sci-fi sequel, starring Danny Glover, Bill Paxton, Gary Busey and Maria Conchita Alonso.

programme.title: Transcendence
programme.desc: A scientist working to develop artificial intelligence is assassinated, but his death provides the breakthrough he and his colleagues needed, as his own mind is uploaded into a computer system. Granted extraordinary knowledge, he begins planning to change the world for the better - with potentially horrific consequences for the human race. Sci-fi drama, starring Johnny Depp, Rebecca Hall and Morgan Freeman.

programme.title: The Top Ten Show 2015
programme.desc: Countdown of the biggest box office hits in Britain and America.

programme.title: Galaxy Quest
programme.desc: The cast of a cancelled sci-fi series are reduced to a life of conventions and public appearances, only to find themselves genuinely transported into space. Naive aliens have mistaken the show for real life and want the actors to help defend them from an evil extraterrestrial warlord. Sci-fi comedy, starring Tim Allen, Sigourney Weaver, Alan Rickman and Sam Rockwell.

programme.title: Oculus
programme.desc: A woman is reunited with her brother, who was committed to a mental hospital after killing their father, who had tortured and murdered their mother. She believes that a haunted mirror caused their deaths, and takes him back to the site of the tragedy in the hope of confronting the supernatural forces. Horror, starring Karen Gillan, Brenton Thwaites and Katee Sackhoff.

programme.title: March of the Penguins
programme.desc: Luc Jacquet's Oscar-winning nature documentary follows a colony of emperor penguins on a journey hundreds of miles across the Antarctic ice to reach their breeding grounds, enduring harsh weather conditions and freezing temperatures along the way. Once they have mated, the males stay to guard the eggs while the females return to the sea to gather food. Narrated by Morgan Freeman.

programme.title: Boyhood Special
programme.desc: Alex Zane talks to director Richard Linklater about his new movie, filmed over the course of 12 years and following a boy as he grows up.

programme.title: Boyhood
programme.desc: A boy goes through a series of changes in his life, beginning as a six-year-old facing a reunion with his estranged father and a move to a new house. As he grows up, the youngster deals with further upheavals that shape his view of the world. Richard Linklater's drama filmed over the course of 12 years, starring Ellar Coltrane, Patricia Arquette and Ethan Hawke.

programme.title: Nebraska
programme.desc: An elderly alcoholic is mistakenly convinced he has won a sweepstakes prize, and keeps trying to travel from his Montana home to Nebraska to collect it. His son ultimately agrees to drive him there despite knowing it is pointless, but the journey ends abruptly when they become stranded in the town where the old man was born. Drama, starring Bruce Dern and Will Forte.

programme.title: Black Snake Moan
programme.desc: A self-destructive nymphomaniac ends up badly beaten and left for dead by the side of the road. She is rescued by a devoutly religious former blues musician, who nurses her back to health - then keeps her chained up in his home as he tries to save her soul. Drama, starring Christina Ricci, Samuel L Jackson, Justin Timberlake and S Epatha Merkerson.

programme.title: Million Dollar Baby
programme.desc: A down-on-his-luck boxing coach nurses a grudge because his best fighter has abandoned him for the big time. When a 31-year-old waitress turns up asking him to train her, he refuses outright. However, her persistence wins him round and the pair go on to form a strong professional partnership and successful career. Oscar-winning drama, directed by and starring Clint Eastwood, alongside Hilary Swank, Morgan Freeman and Anthony Mackie.

programme.title: The Last Wagon
programme.desc: A mixed-race renegade is convicted for the murder of his wife's killers and transported to prison in a wagon train. When the party is attacked by Apaches, the only survivors are the prisoner and a group of orphaned children, so he takes responsibility for leading them to safety. Western, with Richard Widmark, Felicia Farr, Ray Stricklyn and Susan Kohner.

programme.title: Night at the Museum: Battle of the Smithsonian
programme.desc: The living exhibits at New York's Museum of Natural History are shipped to Washington's Smithsonian Institution - along with the artefact that brought them to life in the first place. Nightwatchman Larry tries to retrieve it, only to find the contents of the world's largest museum have been reanimated, including a pharaoh determined to take over the world. Fantasy comedy sequel, starring Ben Stiller, Amy Adams, Owen Wilson and Steve Coogan.

programme.title: The Rugrats Movie
programme.desc: Tommy tries to return his new brother to the baby shop, helped by Angelica, Chuckie, Phil and Lil - but the friends get lost in dense woodlands en route, turning their expedition into a scary and exciting journey of discovery. Animated comedy based on the TV series, with the voices of Elizabeth Daily, Christine Cavanaugh, Kath Soucie, Whoopi Goldberg and Busta Rhymes.

programme.title: New in Town
programme.desc: A Miami business executive accepts a temporary assignment helping to downsize a manufacturing plant in a small Minnesota town. Despite a frosty reception, she soon finds herself warming to the community and falling in love with the man of her dreams - until she is asked to do the unthinkable. Romantic comedy, starring Renee Zellweger, Harry Connick Jr and JK Simmons.

programme.title: Macbeth Interview Special
programme.desc: Michael Fassbender, Marion Cotillard and director Justin Kurzel talk about making the new screen version of Macbeth.

programme.title: The Perks of Being a Wallflower
programme.desc: An introverted 15-year-old fails to fit in at a 1990s high school as he copes with personal traumas and his own social awkwardness. He finally finds a place to belong when two older students take him under their wing. Drama based on director Stephen Chbosky's novel, starring Logan Lerman, Emma Watson and Ezra Miller.

programme.title: Sicario Interview Special
programme.desc: Emily Blunt and Benicio Del Toro join director Denis Villeneuve to talk about the making of their drug-cartel drama Sicario.

programme.title: Taken
programme.desc: An American teenager travelling through Europe is abducted by a gang of sex traffickers. However, what the kidnappers do not realise is that the girl's father is a former CIA agent, who employs all his old skills as he searches for the criminals and tries to rescue his daughter. Thriller, starring Liam Neeson, Famke Janssen and Maggie Grace.

programme.title: Machete
programme.desc: A Mexican cop-turned-mercenary is hired by a shadowy businessman to assassinate a politician. When he realises his employers have double-crossed him, he joins forces with a band of militant illegal immigrants to seek a suitably bloody revenge. Action thriller, starring Danny Trejo, Robert De Niro and Jessica Alba.

programme.title: A Song for the Season
programme.desc: An inspirational music teacher throws herself into preparing her students for a tuneful extravaganza. However, she remains blissfully unaware that the school is in financial difficulty and plan to close the music department. A dour administrator is sent to oversee the school's fate, only to face a crisis of conscience when he falls for the teacher. Romantic drama, starring Naomi Judd, Gerald McRaney and Alison Pill.

programme.title: A Holiday to Remember
programme.desc: A single mum returns to her childhood home where she intends to escape from the pressures of life in Los Angeles - until an old boyfriend persuades her to rekindle the flames of their passion. Romantic drama, with Connie Sellecca, Randy Travis, Asia Vieria and Rue McClanahan.

programme.title: My Husband's Double Life
programme.desc: Fact-based drama focusing on an ex-convict who fakes his own death, leaving his unsuspecting family devastated while he makes a fresh start. However, after 10 years of life as a single mother, his downtrodden wife finally stumbles on the truth. Starring Margaret Colin, Jay O Sanders and Michael Cera.

programme.title: A Christmas Romance
programme.desc: A selfish banker visits a single mother with the intention of repossessing her house, but his plans go awry as a snowstorm forces him to stay there and romance begins to blossom. Family drama, starring Olivia Newton-John and Gregory Harrison.

programme.title: A Different Kind of Christmas
programme.desc: A lawyer dreams of an illustrious career, but her ambitions are jeopardised by her elderly father, who is convinced he really is Santa Claus. Drama, starring Shelley Long, Barry Bostwick, Nathan Lawrence and Bruce Kirby.

programme.title: The Christmas List
programme.desc: A shop assistant is frustrated at her lack of success at work and fed up with her boyfriend taking her for granted. She writes a list of the things she wants out of life, which ends up in the shop's mailbox for children's letters to Santa. Magically, her wishes start coming true, but not always in the way she hoped. Fantasy drama, starring Mimi Rogers, Rob Stewart and Stella Stevens.

programme.title: The Christmas Box
programme.desc: A hard-working man's obsession with his business causes him to neglect his family - but a series of strange dreams makes him realise it is the most important thing in his life. Drama, starring Richard Thomas and Maureen O'Hara.

programme.title: Ebbie
programme.desc: A high-flying but mean-hearted female department store executive is brought back down to earth with a bump by three spooks determined to put a smile on her face in preparation for the Christmas season's celebrations. Festive drama, starring Susan Lucci, Wendy Crewson, Ron Lea, Jeffrey DeMunn and Molly Parker.

programme.title: Naughty or Nice
programme.desc: A controversial radio host crosses the line by upsetting a seriously ill teenager who is trying to stay cheerful in the face of adversity. The public backlash is so strong that the bullying broadcaster is obliged to mend his ways and behave nicely to everyone for one whole day. Christmas comedy, starring George Lopez, James Kirk, Lisa Vidal and Bianca Collins.

programme.title: Conspiracy Exposed: The James Thornwell Story
programme.desc: Fact-based drama about a US soldier who was the victim of torture by his own side, and was also administered drugs to him without his knowledge as part of an experiment. Starring Glynn Turman and Vincent Gardenia.

programme.title: Crimes of Passion: Victim of Love
programme.desc: A sinister killer marries then murders a naive woman, prompting her parents to begin a relentless fight to bring him to justice. Fact-based drama, with Dwight Schultz, Bonnie Bartlett, Andy Romano and Dennis Boutsikaris.

programme.title: The Waltons
programme.desc: Part one of two. The family mourns Grandpa's death and celebrates his life, while Mary Ellen and Erin become roommates in Charlottesville.

programme.title: The Waltons
programme.desc: Part two of two. The family mourns Grandpa's death and celebrates his life, while Mary Ellen and Erin become roommates in Charlottesville.

programme.title: Danielle Steel's Kaleidoscope
programme.desc: Three young sisters and their brother are orphaned in early childhood, and while three of them are found loving and protective homes, one suffers a life of neglect and poverty. Thirty years later they are reunited, but the elder sister has a shocking secret she needs to share. Drama based on a novel by Danielle Steel, starring Jaclyn Smith, Perry King, Colleen Dewhurst and Claudia Christian.

programme.title: The Fallen Idol
programme.desc: An ambassador's son idolises his father's butler, and tries to throw the police off his scent when he is suspected of murder. However, the boy's actions only make the servant seem more suspicious, and he begins to realise that his hero may have deceived him. Crime drama, starring Ralph Richardson and Bobby Henrey.

programme.title: Billy Liar
programme.desc: A bored undertaker's clerk in a 1950s northern town daydreams of an imaginary world to escape from his dull life, while struggling to keep his two fiancees from finding out about each other. When an old girlfriend returns to the area, she offers him a fresh start, if he is brave enough to leave his fantasies behind. Drama, starring Tom Courtenay and Julie Christie.

programme.title: Anybody's Nightmare
programme.desc: A day trip leads to nightmare as an elderly woman is found dead in suspicious circumstances, and the finger of blame points squarely at her respectable niece. Drama based on the true story of piano teacher Sheila Fowler, whose conviction for murder on the age-old grounds of greed led to a life sentence only overturned by years of tireless campaigning on the part of her friends. Starring Patricia Routledge and Georgina Sutcliffe.

programme.title: The Wipers Times
programme.desc: In the bombed-out ruins of the Belgian town of Ypres in 1916, Captain Fred Roberts and Lieutenant Jack Pearson discover a printing press and decide to start a satirical newspaper to raise the spirits of the British troops. It proves hugely popular with the men in the trenches - but their superior officers see it as an act of insubordination and subversion and call for a ban. Feature-length factual drama by Ian Hislop and Nick Newman, starring Ben Chaplin, Julian Rhind-Tutt, Michael Palin and Emilia Fox.

programme.title: Daddy's Girl
programme.desc: A landscape gardener finally finds new romance 10 years after his wife walked out - but as a result, his teenage daughter begins to suffer recurring nightmares about the night her mum disappeared. Turning to the police for help, she claims a murder has taken place, and a full investigation into the case begins - but suspicions remain that she is merely manipulating her dad. Drama, starring Martin Kemp.

programme.title: Common
programme.desc: One-off drama from Jimmy McGovern, exploring the possible consequences of the UK's Joint Enterprise law, by which more than one person can be charged with the same offence. Seventeen-year-old Johnjo gives his cousin Tony and some friends a lift to a pizza parlour for food, unaware their real intention is to `sort out' a local loudmouth. Things soon get out of hand, however, and an innocent bystander is fatally stabbed - and despite being in the car all the time, Johnjo finds himself charged with murder along with everyone else. Nico Mirallegro heads a cast that also includes Susan Lynch, Daniel Mays, Jodhi May, Robert Pugh and Michelle Fairley.

programme.title: Carrington
programme.desc: Fact-based drama, chronicling the relationship between Bloomsbury group artist Dora Carrington and homosexual writer Lytton Strachey during the 1920s. Starring Emma Thompson, Jonathan Pryce, Samuel West, Rufus Sewell, Penelope Wilton, Steven Waddington, Peter Blythe, Janet McTeer, Jeremy Northam and Alex Kingston.

programme.desc: Adrien Broner (30-2, 22 KOs) takes on Khabib Allakhverdiev (19-1, 9 KOs) in the main event. Also: Edner Cherry (34-6, 19 KO) vs. Jose Pedraza (20-0, 12 KO). From Cincinnati. All the latest fights and action

programme.desc: A street racer recently released from prison, after being framed by a rich business associate, joins a cross country race with plans for revenge

programme.title: Runaway Bride
programme.desc: A disreputable journalist hopes to get his ailing career back on track by writing an article about a woman famed for her deep-seated fear of commitment - but complications arise as the duo meet on the eve of her fourth wedding attempt. Sometimes complacent, but still sparky romantic comedy from Garry Marshall, the director of Pretty Woman - who is reunited here with the stars of that blockbuster, Julia Roberts and Richard Gere. Joan Cusack, Hector Elizondo and Rita Wilson provide more than capable support

CIA drama, starring Claire Danes, Rupert Friend, Mandy Patinkin and Nazanin Boniadi. Political thriller starring Clare Danes as a CIA agent with bipolar disorder

US drama, starring Claire Danes and Tracy Letts. Political thriller starring Clare Danes as a CIA agent with bipolar disorder
